                            <comment id="14153286" author="knoguchi" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 16:32:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;One of our users has a logic in their script that requires LIMIT on 0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This user wants to store at most N outputs total from contentA and contentB.  Giving preference on contentA. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;limitContentA = limit contentA N; 
groupedContent_A = GROUP limitContentA ALL;
limitContentB = limit contentA N - totalStoredContent_A.$0

... store both limitContentA and limitContentB
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14153287" author="knoguchi" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 16:33:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Straightforward patch that accepts 0 variablelimit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14153495" author="daijy" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 19:14:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154269" author="rohini" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 04:18:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you just add a newline before @Test before checking in the patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14155221" author="knoguchi" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 19:07:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 0.14 and trunk (with extra line added pointed out by Rohini).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Daniel and Rohini for the review! &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
